<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="youth-n">youth <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /juːθ/    美 /juːθ/  </p>
<p>(pl youths)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 青少年时代：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He worked with wood during his early youth. 年轻时，他做过木匠。 
</p><footer>北师大② – 6</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-u">2.★ <strong>[U] 青春；朝气：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her face still kept its youth. 
她的面容青春尤驻。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-c">3.★ <strong>[C] 青年男子； 小伙子</strong></h4>
<h4 id="4-the">4.★ <strong>[集合名词，常与the连用] 年轻人；青年：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>The youth of today</strong> has / have greater opportunities than ever before. 
现在的年轻人拥有的机会比以往任何时候都要多。</p></div></div>